STA 2453 Project 1 - Condos Model

Ruiwen Wang, Charlie Yu, Chenghui Zheng

December 2, 2020

Goal & Motivation

Our group chose to analyze condo listing data from Condos.ca.

The goal is to help better understand the properties that affect Toronto condo market for both selling and renting.

We will talk about:

  • Data Collection
  • Data Preparation
  • Exploratory Analysis
  • Time Series Analysis
  • Modeling

Data Collection

The website is free to browse as long as you sign up. Also there will be an agent contacting you directly to help you find condos.

Use web scrapping to import data:

  • All current listings as of Nov 13, 2020
  • Geography Bound: GTA region
  • Past data to conduct time series analysis
  • Split the data into Rent and Sale

Conclusion

  • Key factors include: neighbourhood, sqft, bed, bathrooms, # of photos uploaded, property type, distance to TTC and interactions between them
  • For most of the factors, linear trend with a limit
  • Also tried modeling log of asking price *More details and analysis on Sale data could be found in the report.
